# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js 16.1.6 App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights` package using npm
- Package version: Latest compatible version
- Updated package.json and package-lock.json

### 2. Root Layout Modification (app/layout.tsx)
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag after `{children}`
- Placement ensures Speed Insights tracks all page navigation and performance metrics

## Implementation Details

### Why This Approach?
The project uses:
- Next.js 16.1.6 (well above the 13.5+ requirement for App Router)
- App Router architecture (app/ directory)
- TypeScript

This qualifies for the recommended implementation using `@vercel/speed-insights/next` with automatic route tracking.

### Code Structure
The SpeedInsights component was added to the root layout at `app/layout.tsx`, which wraps all pages in the application. This ensures:
- Automatic tracking of all route transitions
- Performance metrics collection across the entire app
- Minimal code changes with maximum coverage

